Lương Mai Thanh Khôi is an Intern Software Engineer (Web/Mobile) with 0 years of commercial experience. Their core expertise lies in Microservices architecture using Java Spring Boot and ASP.NET Core frameworks, with a strong foundation in Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) and RESTful APIs. They have developed multiple personal projects, including a Real Estate Trading/Rental Web System, which features 5 core services and utilizes Java Spring Boot with MySQL, PostgreSQL, and MongoDB for databases, and a Phone Sales POS Web System built with PHP, demonstrating their ability to design and implement functional web-based systems. Their experience with Thymeleaf for user interface development and Git for version control showcases their proficiency in web development and collaboration tools.

Technically, they are proficient in a range of programming languages, including Java, Python, C, C#, PHP, SQL, and Kotlin, and have hands-on experience with frameworks such as Java Spring, Spring Boot, and ASP.NET Core. They are familiar with databases like MySQL, Firebase, PostgreSQL, and MongoDB, and have worked with cloud platforms like Firebase. Additionally, they have experience with devops tools like Git and have worked with design tools like Figma. Their domain knowledge spans web and mobile development, with a focus on UI/UX design and mobile development for Android. They also possess certifications in MOS Word 2016 and MOS Excel 2016, demonstrating their proficiency in Microsoft Office tools. With a strong educational background in Software Engineering from Tôn Đức Thắng University, Lương Mai Thanh Khôi is well-equipped to tackle complex software engineering challenges and contribute to innovative projects.